Cumulated cases of Coronavirus per 100000 people

source : https://covid19.who.int/data
link to download the data : https://covid19.who.int/WHO-COVID-19-global-table-data.csv

Code

data <- read.csv("/Users/Patrycja/Documents/R_rok2/WHO_covid.csv")
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(maps)
library(mapdata)

world <- map_data("world")
Europe <- c("UK", "Ukraine", "Switzerland", "Sweden", "Spain", "Slovenia", "Slovakia", "Serbia", "Russia",  "Romania", "Portugal", "Poland",    "Norway",   "North Macedonia", "Netherlands", "Montenegro", "Monaco",   "Moldova", "Malta", "Luxembourg",   "Lithuania", "Liechtenstein",    "Latvia"   ,   "Italy" ,   "Ireland"   ,   "Iceland", "Hungary",   "Holy See", "Greece",   "Germany", "France",    "Finland", "Estonia",   "Denmark", "Czech Republic", "Croatia", "Bulgaria", "Bosnia and Herzegovina",   "Belgium",  "Belarus",  "Austria", "Andorra",   "Albania", "Russia", "Kosovo")
Europedf <- data.frame(region = Europe)

covid <- data %>% 
  filter(WHO_Region == "Europe" & Name %in% Europe) %>%  
  select(Name, Cases...cumulative.total.per.100000.population)

map <- world %>% right_join(covid, by = c("region" = "Name"))

eu_base <- ggplot(data = map, mapping = aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) + 
  coord_fixed(1.3) + 
  geom_polygon(color = "#737373", fill = "gray") +
  theme(
  axis.text = element_blank(),
  axis.line = element_blank(),
  axis.ticks = element_blank(),
  panel.border = element_blank(),
  axis.title = element_blank()
)

eu_base + 
  geom_polygon(data = map, aes(fill = Cases...cumulative.total.per.100000.population), color = "white") +
  geom_polygon(color = "#737373", fill = NA) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(title = "Cumulated cases of Coronavirus in Europe per 100000 people",
       subtitle = "with 3 countries with the highest value marked",
       fill = "Cases per 100000 people")+
  theme(
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#ffffe5"),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "#ffffe5"),
    legend.background = element_rect(fill = "#ffffe5"),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 15, colour = "#cc4c02", face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 13, colour = "#cc4c02", face = "bold", hjust = 0.5))+
  scale_fill_gradient2(
  low = "#fed976",
  mid = "#fd8d3c",
  high = "#b10026",
  midpoint = 35450.49,
  guide = "colourbar",
  aesthetics = "fill"
)-> final

points <- as.data.frame(map) %>% 
  group_by(region) %>% 
  summarise(long = mean(long), lat = mean(lat), names = (paste(as.character(Cases...cumulative.total.per.100000.population), as.character(region), sep = " - ")), group = group) 

points2 <- Europedf %>% left_join(points, by = c("region" = "region")) %>% 
  unique() %>% 
  arrange(desc(names)) %>% 
  head(3)

final +  
  geom_point(data = points2, aes(x = long, y = lat), color = "black", size = 1.2) +
  geom_text(data = points2, aes(x = long, y = lat-0.5, label = names), color = "black", size = 3.5, fontface = "bold")
